42.body:
With an HTTP response with the following body: { "characters": [ { "type": "Human", "id": "1000", "name": "Luke Skywalker", "friends": ["1002", "1003", "2000", "2001"], "appearsIn": [4, 5, 6], "homePlanet": "Tatooine", }, { "type": "Human", "id": "1001", "name": "Darth Vader", "friends": ["1004"], "appearsIn": [4, 5, 6], "homePlanet": "Tatooine", }, { "type": "Droid", "id": "2001", "name": "R2-D2", "friends": ["1000", "1002", "1003"], "appearsIn": [4, 5, 6], "primaryFunction": "Astromech", } ]
} and our query is defined as: select: name: for_each[0].name
for_each: - response.body.characters The output values would be: { "name": "Luke Skywalker" }, { "name": "Darth Vader" }, { "name": "R2-D2" }.
